Class ContentItemsListingResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kenticocloud.delivery.ContentItemsListingResponse

  • public class ContentItemsListingResponse
extends java.lang.Object
    Content items listing response

    When you retrieve a list of content items from your project, the Delivery API returns a ContentItemsListingResponse

    See Also:
    DeliveryClient.getItems(), DeliveryClient.getItems(List)

      • castTo

        public <T> java.util.List<T> castTo(java.lang.Class<T> tClass)
        Returns a new instance of List<T> by mapping fields to elements in this content item. Element fields are mapped by automatically CamelCasing and checking for equality, unless otherwise annotated by an ElementMapping annotation. T must have a default constructor and have standard setter methods.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of class
        Parameters:
        tClass - The class which a new instance should be returned from
        Returns:
        An instance of List<T> with data mapped from the ContentItem list in this response.
